						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 7 <hi rend="italic">kaḷañju (tuḷaippoṉ)</hi> of gold and a lamp-stand for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirumūlaṭṭānattu-Perumānaḍigaḷ at Tirunalakkuṉṟam in Kuṉṟiyūr-nāḍu by one <hi rend="bold">Śaṅkaraṉ Kuṉṟappoḻāṉ of Malai-nāḍu.</hi> This is probably a record of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi> (No. 58, <hi rend="italic">Pud. Ins.</hi> Texts.)</p>						

						</summary>
